entry.title: [blink] Remove check for IsLost() when CanvasResource destroys resources
entry.content:
We want to be guaranteed that the destruction of the SharedImage here is

actually occurring via this call. At present, the check for IsLost() is

the only meaningful thing preventing that (the other checks are that

either the entire SII was already torn down or that the SharedImage was

never successfully created in the first place). This check was added as

part of a speculative fix for a ClusterFuzz bug (crbug.com/1433545). The

same CL added the check for IsValid(), which is what actually fixed the

bug. IsLost() doesn't mean that the resource shouldn't be destroyed, but

rather just that it shouldn't be reused.

entry.title: QuickStart: Use Base64 type for FIDO credential id
entry.content:
Use Base64 as the type of FIDO credential id instead of std::string.

This will help us prevent encoding bugs. It is impossible to guess the

encoding of a std::string data, and can lead to double-encoding or

no-encoding bugs.



Additionally, use Base64 instead of Base64Url as the underlying encoding

(see https://crrev.com/c/5013510). This follows the encoding guideline

at https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/proto3/#json. GoogleFE /

OnePlatform is lenient in allowing Base64Url representation of byte

array proto fields, but the canonical representation is still Base64

(not Base64Url).

entry.title: [//ash] Allow UiResource to take in ClientSharedImage
entry.content:
UiResource has two modes of operation with respect to the SharedImage

that it holds a reference to:



1. It owns the SharedImage and is responsible for calling

DestroySharedImage()

2. It does *not* own the SharedImage and should not call

DestroySharedImage()



This CL separates out these two cases explicitly by having UiResource

take in a scoped_refptr in the first case and

a gpu::Mailbox in the second case. This will allow clients of UiResource

that will need to access its ClientSharedImage to do so in followup

work (e.g., for converting MapSharedImage() from taking in a Mailbox to

taking in a ClientSharedImage).



Note that it is not viable to pass in ClientSharedImage in case 2:

- FastInkHost will call DestroySharedImage() on the ClientSI

- DestroySharedImage() CHECKs that there is only one reference on the

passed-in ClientSI

- The UiResources outlive FastInkHost, as they are destroyed in its

base class destructor



This CL also changes UiResource to call DestroySharedImage(ClientSI)

rather than DestroySharedImage(Mailbox) in the case where it is holding

a ClientSharedImage. This change is guaranteed to be safe as UiResource

does not give out its `client_si_`, so that ivar is guaranteed to be the

only reference to the ClientSharedImage.

entry.title: [bookmarks] Let unit-tests load BookmarkModel without TestBookmarkClient
entry.content:
There is no reason to enforce that

TestBookmarkClient::CreateModelWithClient() is the only way, via class

friendship, to load a BookmarkModel synchronously in unit-tests.



In fact, it makes more sense that

TestBookmarkClient::CreateModelWithClient() is exclusively limited to

the passed client being a TestBookmarkClient, rather any arbitrary

BookmarkClient.



There is exactly one test that uses another subclass of BookmarkClient

that isn't TestBookmarkClient, under components/power_bookmarks. For

cases like this, it seems more appropriate to offer test-only helpers

outside TestBookmarkClient. Namely, in this patch, BookmarkModel itself

is extended with LoadEmptyForTest(), which avoids friend classes and is

exclusively meant for unit-tests.



This also allows tackling quite naturally a longstanding TODO about

ModelLoader being bypassed in tests.

entry.title: Prerender: Change FindReservedHostById() to HasReservedHost()
entry.content:
This is a pure cleanup, and doesn't change functional behavior.



For PrerenderHostRegistry::FindReservedHostById(), its name doesn't

match actual function behavior. Only one reserved PrerenderHost exists

per PrerenderHostRegistry, so the function just accesses the member

field, not *find* it somewhere. Also, this function is now used only for

checking if some host is reserved, so the function doesn't need to

return a pointer to the reserved host. To reflect the actual behavior

and usage, this CL changes FindReservedHostById() to HasReservedHost()

that just returns a boolean to indicate if the reserved host exists.



For PrerenderNewTabHandle::GetPrerenderHostForTesting(), this is no

longer used after https://crrev.com/c/5016385, so this CL removes it.
